[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:17.465 --> 00:00:24.179 align:middle line:90%


00:00:24.179 --> 00:00:26.220 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE NOORY: Well,
welcome to "Beyond Belief."

00:00:26.220 --> 00:00:27.090 align:middle line:10%
I'm George Noory.

00:00:27.090 --> 00:00:28.881 align:middle line:10%
And what a program we
have in store for you

00:00:28.881 --> 00:00:32.580 align:middle line:10%
today, as we talk about the life
of the late American profit,

00:00:32.580 --> 00:00:34.770 align:middle line:10%
Edgar Cayce, with
Kevin Todeschi.

00:00:34.770 --> 00:00:38.190 align:middle line:84%
Kevin, of course, is the
CEO executive director

00:00:38.190 --> 00:00:40.380 align:middle line:90%
of the Edgar Cayce foundation--

00:00:40.380 --> 00:00:44.100 align:middle line:84%
ARE, Association for
Research and Enlightenment--

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:46.920 align:middle line:84%
and also Atlantic University
and a noted author

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:48.310 align:middle line:90%
with about 25 books.

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:49.950 align:middle line:90%
Kevin, welcome to the program.

00:00:49.950 --> 00:00:51.510 align:middle line:90%
And it's great to see you live.

00:00:51.510 --> 00:00:53.635 align:middle line:84%
>>KEVIN TODESCHI: Thanks
for having me on the show.

00:00:53.635 --> 00:00:55.590 align:middle line:84%
You have generated
so much publicity

00:00:55.590 --> 00:00:58.020 align:middle line:84%
when you're on the "Coast
to Coast" radio show.

00:00:58.020 --> 00:00:59.687 align:middle line:84%
It's great to see you
live and personal.

00:00:59.687 --> 00:01:01.311 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
thanks for having me.

00:01:01.311 --> 00:01:03.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now tell me a little
bit about your involvement

00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:07.110 align:middle line:84%
with Edgar Cayce, a
fascinating individual.

00:01:07.110 --> 00:01:09.750 align:middle line:90%
We call him the American profit.

00:01:09.750 --> 00:01:11.910 align:middle line:84%
We'll get into some
of the things he did.

00:01:11.910 --> 00:01:13.392 align:middle line:90%
But how did you get involved?

00:01:13.392 --> 00:01:15.100 align:middle line:10%
>>TODESCHI: When I
was in the 11th grade,

00:01:15.100 --> 00:01:17.940 align:middle line:10%
I went to a week-long program
at Colorado State University.

00:01:17.940 --> 00:01:20.075 align:middle line:10%
And while there, I
went to a bookstore.

00:01:20.075 --> 00:01:21.450 align:middle line:10%
And the book that
stood out to me

00:01:21.450 --> 00:01:25.020 align:middle line:10%
was a book by Jess Stearn,
"A Profit in his Own Country,

00:01:25.020 --> 00:01:26.430 align:middle line:10%
The Story of Young Edgar Cayce."

00:01:26.430 --> 00:01:28.590 align:middle line:84%
And when I read
that book, I knew

00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:30.670 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to work at
ARE from that time on.

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:33.420 align:middle line:84%
So after I graduated from
the University of Colorado,

00:01:33.420 --> 00:01:34.950 align:middle line:90%
I moved right to Virginia Beach.

00:01:34.950 --> 00:01:37.350 align:middle line:84%
And I have been on staff
there for the last 36 years.

00:01:37.350 --> 00:01:38.409 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: You were hooked.

00:01:38.409 --> 00:01:39.450 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: I was hooked.

00:01:39.450 --> 00:01:41.971 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Tell us a little bit
about who Edgar Cayce was.

00:01:41.971 --> 00:01:44.220 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Edgar Cayce is
the most documented psychic

00:01:44.220 --> 00:01:45.180 align:middle line:90%
of all time.

00:01:45.180 --> 00:01:48.910 align:middle line:90%
He lived between 1877 and 1945.

00:01:48.910 --> 00:01:52.230 align:middle line:84%
For 43 years of his adult
life, he put himself to sleep,

00:01:52.230 --> 00:01:53.250 align:middle line:90%
closed his eyes.

00:01:53.250 --> 00:01:55.620 align:middle line:84%
He could be given the
name and address of anyone

00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:58.140 align:middle line:84%
anywhere in the world,
tune into that person.

00:01:58.140 --> 00:02:00.990 align:middle line:84%
And he could outline any kind
of questions they might ask.

00:02:00.990 --> 00:02:01.950 align:middle line:90%
How can I get well?

00:02:01.950 --> 00:02:04.210 align:middle line:84%
How can I improve
my relationships?

00:02:04.210 --> 00:02:06.180 align:middle line:90%
What's my soul's purpose?

00:02:06.180 --> 00:02:07.980 align:middle line:90%
What can I do about this issue?

00:02:07.980 --> 00:02:11.130 align:middle line:84%
And the responses to those
questions are called readings.

00:02:11.130 --> 00:02:14.280 align:middle line:84%
The Cayce Database consists
of 24 million words

00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:16.060 align:middle line:90%
and 10,000 different topics.

00:02:16.060 --> 00:02:18.070 align:middle line:84%
So it's an incredible
source of information.

00:02:18.070 --> 00:02:19.445 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Well,
they say a picture

00:02:19.445 --> 00:02:20.620 align:middle line:90%
is worth a thousand words.

00:02:20.620 --> 00:02:23.070 align:middle line:84%
So let's find out a little
bit more about Edgar Cayce.

00:02:23.070 --> 00:02:26.542 align:middle line:90%


00:02:26.542 --> 00:02:29.518 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:29.518 --> 00:02:32.500 align:middle line:90%


00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:35.200 align:middle line:84%
>> He has been called
the sleeping prophet,

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:39.070 align:middle line:84%
a man of miracles,
a see-er, a mystic.

00:02:39.070 --> 00:02:41.710 align:middle line:84%
His work is known
around the globe.

00:02:41.710 --> 00:02:45.380 align:middle line:84%
Hundreds of books have explored
his amazing psychic gift.

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:49.270 align:middle line:84%
From medical diagnoses to
predicting social change,

00:02:49.270 --> 00:02:53.620 align:middle line:84%
Edgar Cayce's legacy has
touched the lives of millions.

00:02:53.620 --> 00:02:56.980 align:middle line:84%
For 43 years of his
adult life, Edgar Cayce

00:02:56.980 --> 00:03:01.390 align:middle line:84%
gave psychic readings on more
than 10,000 different subjects.

00:03:01.390 --> 00:03:05.050 align:middle line:84%
Nearly everything imaginable
is explored in his material--

00:03:05.050 --> 00:03:08.920 align:middle line:84%
healing, business advice,
the Bible, education,

00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:12.220 align:middle line:84%
child rearing,
ancient civilizations,

00:03:12.220 --> 00:03:18.480 align:middle line:84%
spirituality, prophecy of
world events, and much more.

00:03:18.480 --> 00:03:19.370 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:03:19.370 --> 00:03:23.240 align:middle line:84%
>> He looked like a country
doctor, a simple person.

00:03:23.240 --> 00:03:26.030 align:middle line:84%
You wouldn't turn around in
the street if you saw him.

00:03:26.030 --> 00:03:30.000 align:middle line:84%
But once you spoke to
him, his voice was soft.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:31.730 align:middle line:90%
It was direct.

00:03:31.730 --> 00:03:32.690 align:middle line:90%
It was honest.

00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:34.070 align:middle line:90%
It was embracing.

00:03:34.070 --> 00:03:38.960 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I always saw a
double pupil, a superimposure,

00:03:38.960 --> 00:03:41.570 align:middle line:84%
as if he were looking
through eternity.

00:03:41.570 --> 00:03:43.411 align:middle line:84%
It made you a little
uncomfortable at times.

00:03:43.411 --> 00:03:45.410 align:middle line:84%
Because you wondered what
you had done yesterday

00:03:45.410 --> 00:03:47.260 align:middle line:84%
or said yesterday that you
ought not to have said.

00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:47.490 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:03:47.490 --> 00:03:49.580 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Kevin, he was
the real deal, wasn't he?

00:03:49.580 --> 00:03:50.954 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: He
was the real deal.

00:03:50.954 --> 00:03:53.727 align:middle line:84%
And his desire was to
be helpful to people.

00:03:53.727 --> 00:03:56.060 align:middle line:84%
Toward the end of his life,
he actually got overwhelmed.

00:03:56.060 --> 00:03:58.619 align:middle line:84%
They used to deliver sacks
of mail to the Cayce home.

00:03:58.619 --> 00:04:01.160 align:middle line:84%
And his own readings had told
him never to give more than two

00:04:01.160 --> 00:04:02.060 align:middle line:90%
a day.

00:04:02.060 --> 00:04:03.890 align:middle line:84%
And he told his
secretary that, just

00:04:03.890 --> 00:04:06.510 align:middle line:84%
by walking by the sacks of
mail, he could feel the pain.

00:04:06.510 --> 00:04:08.660 align:middle line:84%
So he asked her to
book in advance.

00:04:08.660 --> 00:04:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And when he had a stroke, he
was giving eight readings a day.

00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:14.300 align:middle line:84%
And when he died, they were
book two years in advance.

00:04:14.300 --> 00:04:16.610 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Didn't these
readings and the intensity

00:04:16.610 --> 00:04:18.161 align:middle line:84%
of the readings
eventually do him in?

00:04:18.161 --> 00:04:19.160 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: That was it.

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:20.690 align:middle line:84%
It was very much him
tuning into a higher

00:04:20.690 --> 00:04:22.500 align:middle line:84%
source of consciousness,
I guess kind of

00:04:22.500 --> 00:04:24.620 align:middle line:84%
like plugging your finger
into a light socket.

00:04:24.620 --> 00:04:26.150 align:middle line:90%
And that just wore him down.

00:04:26.150 --> 00:04:29.540 align:middle line:84%
And the demand for his help
toward the end of his life

00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:30.680 align:middle line:90%
was really overwhelming.

00:04:30.680 --> 00:04:33.055 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: He used to talk a
lot about the Akashic records.

00:04:33.055 --> 00:04:33.854 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: He did.

00:04:33.854 --> 00:04:35.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: What are they?

00:04:35.010 --> 00:04:38.180 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well, Akashic comes
from the Sanskrit word Akasha,

00:04:38.180 --> 00:04:39.662 align:middle line:90%
which means boundless space.

00:04:39.662 --> 00:04:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And according to
Edgar Cayce, there

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:43.730 align:middle line:84%
is this etheric field
around the Earth that

00:04:43.730 --> 00:04:46.040 align:middle line:84%
basically contains
everything that has ever

00:04:46.040 --> 00:04:47.360 align:middle line:90%
been done in the Earth.

00:04:47.360 --> 00:04:51.054 align:middle line:84%
And according to Cayce,
your thoughts, your deeds,

00:04:51.054 --> 00:04:52.220 align:middle line:90%
everything's recorded there.

00:04:52.220 --> 00:04:54.332 align:middle line:84%
And as unusual as
that may sound--

00:04:54.332 --> 00:04:55.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure many of
your listeners are

00:04:55.790 --> 00:04:58.220 align:middle line:84%
aware of that near-death
experience, where someone dies,

00:04:58.220 --> 00:04:59.840 align:middle line:84%
and then they have
a life review.

00:04:59.840 --> 00:05:00.950 align:middle line:84%
Cayce would say,
you're actually tuning

00:05:00.950 --> 00:05:02.180 align:middle line:90%
into your own Akashic record.

00:05:02.180 --> 00:05:04.790 align:middle line:84%
It's a record of everything
that the soul has done

00:05:04.790 --> 00:05:06.200 align:middle line:90%
since its come into the Earth.

00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:07.959 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can we
change those records?

00:05:07.959 --> 00:05:09.750 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: That's an
interesting question.

00:05:09.750 --> 00:05:13.500 align:middle line:84%
And I think it is possible that
you can change those records.

00:05:13.500 --> 00:05:15.470 align:middle line:84%
Another topic in the
readings is essentially

00:05:15.470 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:90%
the illusion of time.

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:19.970 align:middle line:84%
But Cayce suggests
it's possible to alter

00:05:19.970 --> 00:05:22.010 align:middle line:84%
the records of the
future, what's happening

00:05:22.010 --> 00:05:23.190 align:middle line:90%
to you in the present.

00:05:23.190 --> 00:05:25.220 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's even
possible somehow to change

00:05:25.220 --> 00:05:26.330 align:middle line:90%
the records of the past.

00:05:26.330 --> 00:05:28.205 align:middle line:10%
>>NOORY: What's fascinating,
Kevin, is that--

00:05:28.205 --> 00:05:31.280 align:middle line:10%
I was growing up as
a Roman Catholic,

00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:33.680 align:middle line:10%
going to catechism
classes, they always

00:05:33.680 --> 00:05:36.080 align:middle line:10%
talked to us about
"The Good Book,"

00:05:36.080 --> 00:05:39.380 align:middle line:10%
that when you died there'd
be that book of your records.

00:05:39.380 --> 00:05:40.630 align:middle line:90%
It's the same thing, isn't it?

00:05:40.630 --> 00:05:42.200 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: The Bible
calls it The Book of Life

00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:43.770 align:middle line:90%
or God's Book of Remembrance.

00:05:43.770 --> 00:05:45.630 align:middle line:90%
It's definitely the same thing.

00:05:45.630 --> 00:05:46.670 align:middle line:90%
It's the soul's journey.

00:05:46.670 --> 00:05:50.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When you pass and
you get up to that point

00:05:50.960 --> 00:05:54.500 align:middle line:84%
before they decide to send
you to heaven or hell,

00:05:54.500 --> 00:05:57.380 align:middle line:84%
is there somebody there,
like a spirit guide, who

00:05:57.380 --> 00:06:01.700 align:middle line:84%
flips through the pages going,
George, when you were eight,

00:06:01.700 --> 00:06:03.310 align:middle line:90%
remember you did this?

00:06:03.310 --> 00:06:04.310 align:middle line:90%
Is it like that?

00:06:04.310 --> 00:06:07.192 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well, perhaps
not exactly like that.

00:06:07.192 --> 00:06:08.900 align:middle line:84%
But I would say it's
kind of like you get

00:06:08.900 --> 00:06:10.550 align:middle line:90%
to see a review of your life.

00:06:10.550 --> 00:06:14.270 align:middle line:84%
And thankfully, Cayce said that
you get credit for your intent.

00:06:14.270 --> 00:06:16.040 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes, we have
the right intent,

00:06:16.040 --> 00:06:17.340 align:middle line:90%
but things don't work out.

00:06:17.340 --> 00:06:18.590 align:middle line:90%
We get credit for your intent.

00:06:18.590 --> 00:06:20.180 align:middle line:90%
You get credit for the try.

00:06:20.180 --> 00:06:23.170 align:middle line:84%
And I think, very often, we
try to do the right thing,

00:06:23.170 --> 00:06:24.170 align:middle line:90%
but it doesn't work out.

00:06:24.170 --> 00:06:27.080 align:middle line:84%
He also said that, if we do
something with the wrong intent

00:06:27.080 --> 00:06:29.600 align:middle line:84%
and it works out great, we
don't get credit for that.

00:06:29.600 --> 00:06:30.470 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: We don't
get credit for that.

00:06:30.470 --> 00:06:31.280 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: No, we don't
get credit for that.

00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:33.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: But if somebody--

00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:37.300 align:middle line:84%
let's just say a serial killer,
for lack of a better phrase--

00:06:37.300 --> 00:06:39.310 align:middle line:84%
is doing what they
do on this planet,

00:06:39.310 --> 00:06:41.230 align:middle line:90%
which are horrendous things--

00:06:41.230 --> 00:06:44.770 align:middle line:84%
horrendous things-- what
happens when they die?

00:06:44.770 --> 00:06:48.154 align:middle line:84%
And what is their
Akashic record look like?

00:06:48.154 --> 00:06:49.570 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
my understanding

00:06:49.570 --> 00:06:52.670 align:middle line:84%
is that you get to see
your normal life review.

00:06:52.670 --> 00:06:55.070 align:middle line:84%
And then you get to see
the life review again,

00:06:55.070 --> 00:06:59.130 align:middle line:84%
feeling the pain that you cause
for every individual involved.

00:06:59.130 --> 00:07:01.064 align:middle line:84%
So in other words,
if you kill someone,

00:07:01.064 --> 00:07:02.980 align:middle line:84%
you get to experience
the pain of their family

00:07:02.980 --> 00:07:04.060 align:middle line:90%
and their friends.

00:07:04.060 --> 00:07:06.850 align:middle line:84%
And to me, the
intensity of that pain

00:07:06.850 --> 00:07:08.500 align:middle line:84%
would be a horrendous
experience.

00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:11.530 align:middle line:84%
So the soul has to
of its own accord

00:07:11.530 --> 00:07:13.690 align:middle line:84%
take account for
everything its done

00:07:13.690 --> 00:07:15.890 align:middle line:90%
and learn to do differently.

00:07:15.890 --> 00:07:18.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Can you make amends
for your Akashic record?

00:07:18.670 --> 00:07:20.740 align:middle line:84%
By that I mean,
let's assume they

00:07:20.740 --> 00:07:25.150 align:middle line:84%
do some kind of dastardly deed
in their life, but they change.

00:07:25.150 --> 00:07:26.590 align:middle line:90%
They become good people.

00:07:26.590 --> 00:07:28.060 align:middle line:90%
Can that be erased?

00:07:28.060 --> 00:07:30.590 align:middle line:90%
Or is it in that record forever?

00:07:30.590 --> 00:07:34.235 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well, I think you
have to meet the experience so

00:07:34.235 --> 00:07:35.860 align:middle line:84%
that there is an
awareness of something

00:07:35.860 --> 00:07:36.818 align:middle line:90%
that you did was wrong.

00:07:36.818 --> 00:07:38.440 align:middle line:84%
One example that
comes to mind-- there

00:07:38.440 --> 00:07:41.630 align:middle line:84%
was a woman who had been
crippled in the hip.

00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:44.549 align:middle line:84%
She had a real problem in
her hip, pain all her life.

00:07:44.549 --> 00:07:46.090 align:middle line:84%
Cayce gave her a
reading and told her

00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:49.450 align:middle line:84%
that one of her favorite things
to do during the time of Nero

00:07:49.450 --> 00:07:53.290 align:middle line:84%
was go to the arena and watch
the persecution of people

00:07:53.290 --> 00:07:55.690 align:middle line:90%
in the arena being torn apart.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:07:58.820 align:middle line:84%
And Cayce said, and lo that
selfsame thing returns to you.

00:07:58.820 --> 00:08:01.870 align:middle line:84%
So I think there is
an aspect of karma--

00:08:01.870 --> 00:08:04.300 align:middle line:84%
that we have to have an
awareness of something we

00:08:04.300 --> 00:08:06.820 align:middle line:84%
did was wrong, and then
choose differently.

00:08:06.820 --> 00:08:08.170 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Who came up with this?

00:08:08.170 --> 00:08:09.180 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Who came
up with the system?

00:08:09.180 --> 00:08:09.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:08:09.980 --> 00:08:11.680 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: I think it was God.

00:08:11.680 --> 00:08:14.170 align:middle line:84%
It's the system, essentially,
that enables every soul

00:08:14.170 --> 00:08:15.494 align:middle line:90%
to gain enlightenment.

00:08:15.494 --> 00:08:16.660 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: It's well-designed.

00:08:16.660 --> 00:08:17.951 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: It's well-designed.

00:08:17.951 --> 00:08:20.020 align:middle line:90%
There is no loopholes.

00:08:20.020 --> 00:08:22.310 align:middle line:84%
Cayce suggested that,
eventually, every single soul

00:08:22.310 --> 00:08:23.110 align:middle line:90%
will make it.

00:08:23.110 --> 00:08:24.340 align:middle line:90%
It's only a matter of time.

00:08:24.340 --> 00:08:28.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did Cayce ever say
how he got to understand this

00:08:28.930 --> 00:08:30.490 align:middle line:90%
and how he got his abilities?

00:08:30.490 --> 00:08:31.290 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: He did.

00:08:31.290 --> 00:08:33.520 align:middle line:84%
Actually, he had a
series of lifetimes

00:08:33.520 --> 00:08:35.520 align:middle line:90%
where he was extremely psychic.

00:08:35.520 --> 00:08:37.750 align:middle line:84%
And one experience
in ancient Persia,

00:08:37.750 --> 00:08:40.450 align:middle line:84%
he said he had been a
desert nomad who had nearly

00:08:40.450 --> 00:08:41.470 align:middle line:90%
been killed in a battle.

00:08:41.470 --> 00:08:43.929 align:middle line:84%
He had a near-death
experience, left his body.

00:08:43.929 --> 00:08:45.700 align:middle line:84%
And because of that
experience, his mind

00:08:45.700 --> 00:08:47.400 align:middle line:90%
could leave his body now.

00:08:47.400 --> 00:08:49.670 align:middle line:84%
In another experience
in ancient Egypt,

00:08:49.670 --> 00:08:52.480 align:middle line:84%
he had been a high priest that
really worked with attunement,

00:08:52.480 --> 00:08:54.850 align:middle line:84%
and meditation, and could
tune into the secrets

00:08:54.850 --> 00:08:55.880 align:middle line:90%
of the universe.

00:08:55.880 --> 00:08:59.200 align:middle line:84%
And those two experiences really
came with him in the present.

00:08:59.200 --> 00:09:01.720 align:middle line:84%
There was also another one,
where, in the Old West,

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:04.690 align:middle line:84%
he had been what he called a
ne'er-do-well, who used his

00:09:04.690 --> 00:09:07.510 align:middle line:84%
psychic ability to pick
up women and gamble.

00:09:07.510 --> 00:09:09.340 align:middle line:84%
And for that reason,
this time around,

00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:10.930 align:middle line:84%
whenever he gave
a reading, he had

00:09:10.930 --> 00:09:13.990 align:middle line:84%
to put himself to sleep on a
couch to put himself aside.

00:09:13.990 --> 00:09:17.092 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now, that seems like
it was the bad part of his life.

00:09:17.092 --> 00:09:18.550 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: That
was the worst one.

00:09:18.550 --> 00:09:19.540 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, that was the worst.

00:09:19.540 --> 00:09:20.010 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Yeah.

00:09:20.010 --> 00:09:21.627 align:middle line:84%
Well, see, so you
can make amends.

00:09:21.627 --> 00:09:22.960 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: You can make amends.

00:09:22.960 --> 00:09:26.016 align:middle line:84%
You just have to meet everything
and have a change in awareness.

00:09:26.016 --> 00:09:27.640 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did he have
guides or helpers?

00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:30.314 align:middle line:90%


00:09:30.314 --> 00:09:32.230 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: We all have
guides, spirit guides.

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:33.354 align:middle line:90%
We all have angelic guides.

00:09:33.354 --> 00:09:35.580 align:middle line:84%
But he was not
acting like a medium.

00:09:35.580 --> 00:09:37.810 align:middle line:84%
He said he went straight
to the Akashic records

00:09:37.810 --> 00:09:40.430 align:middle line:84%
himself and got the
information firsthand.

00:09:40.430 --> 00:09:42.310 align:middle line:84%
And that way, there
was no intermediary.

00:09:42.310 --> 00:09:45.160 align:middle line:84%
There was no one trying
to decipher or understand

00:09:45.160 --> 00:09:46.290 align:middle line:90%
the information for him.

00:09:46.290 --> 00:09:48.040 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: When he was
in this trance state,

00:09:48.040 --> 00:09:51.312 align:middle line:84%
Kev, was he aware of
what he was saying?

00:09:51.312 --> 00:09:52.270 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: He was not.

00:09:52.270 --> 00:09:55.120 align:middle line:84%
In fact, because he put
himself to sleep, he'd wake up,

00:09:55.120 --> 00:09:57.490 align:middle line:84%
and he'd say, oftentimes,
did you get anything?

00:09:57.490 --> 00:09:59.740 align:middle line:84%
And they'd read them the
transcript of what he did.

00:09:59.740 --> 00:09:59.980 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Wow.

00:09:59.980 --> 00:10:01.990 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Now, later on
towards the end of his life,

00:10:01.990 --> 00:10:03.880 align:middle line:84%
he became very psychic
in the waking state.

00:10:03.880 --> 00:10:05.174 align:middle line:90%
He could see auras.

00:10:05.174 --> 00:10:07.090 align:middle line:84%
He could look at someone
and sometimes pick up

00:10:07.090 --> 00:10:08.379 align:middle line:90%
on their past lives.

00:10:08.379 --> 00:10:10.670 align:middle line:84%
But most of the psychic
ability was in the sleep state.

00:10:10.670 --> 00:10:12.170 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Later on
in the show, we're

00:10:12.170 --> 00:10:14.800 align:middle line:84%
going to have a
reading from Cayce.

00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:18.400 align:middle line:84%
You can actually hear him
in pretty dramatic stuff.

00:10:18.400 --> 00:10:21.282 align:middle line:84%
How long would he stay
under this trance state?

00:10:21.282 --> 00:10:22.990 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: It was
usually under an hour.

00:10:22.990 --> 00:10:25.510 align:middle line:84%
And he would do a reading
in the morning and a reading

00:10:25.510 --> 00:10:27.220 align:middle line:90%
in the afternoon.

00:10:27.220 --> 00:10:29.110 align:middle line:84%
Much of the material
is about health.

00:10:29.110 --> 00:10:31.270 align:middle line:84%
I often say that the
organization is really

00:10:31.270 --> 00:10:33.220 align:middle line:84%
one of the first
self-help organizations,

00:10:33.220 --> 00:10:35.690 align:middle line:84%
helping people transform
themselves physically,

00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:36.850 align:middle line:90%
mentally, and spiritually.

00:10:36.850 --> 00:10:40.180 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: His health reports are
more accurate than most things

00:10:40.180 --> 00:10:41.350 align:middle line:90%
I've ever seen.

00:10:41.350 --> 00:10:44.560 align:middle line:90%
His other ones, ah, so-so--

00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:48.280 align:middle line:84%
like the Edgar Cayce Map of
North America will look like--

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:50.560 align:middle line:84%
it floods in and
everything else.

00:10:50.560 --> 00:10:52.162 align:middle line:90%
But maybe it's timing.

00:10:52.162 --> 00:10:53.620 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
I also say that I

00:10:53.620 --> 00:10:55.245 align:middle line:84%
think there's a lot
of misunderstanding

00:10:55.245 --> 00:10:58.210 align:middle line:84%
about the Cayce information
on, quote, "Earth changes."

00:10:58.210 --> 00:11:00.550 align:middle line:84%
From my premise,
Edgar Cayce didn't

00:11:00.550 --> 00:11:03.790 align:middle line:84%
have a lot of predictions about
problems with Earth changes

00:11:03.790 --> 00:11:04.920 align:middle line:90%
and earthquakes.

00:11:04.920 --> 00:11:06.670 align:middle line:84%
It's just a few
readings that I think

00:11:06.670 --> 00:11:07.990 align:middle line:90%
have been taken out of context.

00:11:07.990 --> 00:11:11.330 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Back to the Akashic
records for just a second--

00:11:11.330 --> 00:11:13.417 align:middle line:84%
when does that book start,
the minute you're born?

00:11:13.417 --> 00:11:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: It started the
minute we were created,

00:11:15.500 --> 00:11:17.749 align:middle line:84%
not just this lifetime but
the moment we were created.

00:11:17.749 --> 00:11:18.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Oh, really?

00:11:18.750 --> 00:11:21.889 align:middle line:84%
So if you've had three
reincarnated lives or 50,

00:11:21.889 --> 00:11:22.930 align:middle line:90%
they're all in this book.

00:11:22.930 --> 00:11:25.690 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: They're all
in there, everything,

00:11:25.690 --> 00:11:28.150 align:middle line:84%
every thought, every
word, every intent.

00:11:28.150 --> 00:11:30.070 align:middle line:84%
And Cayce would say
that, most often, we

00:11:30.070 --> 00:11:32.650 align:middle line:90%
pick up on our karmic memory.

00:11:32.650 --> 00:11:34.354 align:middle line:84%
And it's the memory
we respond to.

00:11:34.354 --> 00:11:35.770 align:middle line:84%
Different people
don't necessarily

00:11:35.770 --> 00:11:36.620 align:middle line:90%
have the same memory.

00:11:36.620 --> 00:11:38.590 align:middle line:84%
It's like, if you have
a spouse and you're both

00:11:38.590 --> 00:11:40.900 align:middle line:84%
describing an incident
that happened 10 years ago,

00:11:40.900 --> 00:11:43.180 align:middle line:84%
you have very different
memories of that experience.

00:11:43.180 --> 00:11:45.670 align:middle line:84%
So we take with this
our own karmic memory.

00:11:45.670 --> 00:11:48.190 align:middle line:90%
And one of my favorite stories--

00:11:48.190 --> 00:11:50.600 align:middle line:84%
John Jay was a founder
of this country.

00:11:50.600 --> 00:11:53.440 align:middle line:84%
He was one of the writers
of the Federalist Papers.

00:11:53.440 --> 00:11:55.907 align:middle line:84%
He was a Chief Justice
of the US Supreme Court.

00:11:55.907 --> 00:11:57.490 align:middle line:84%
There is a biography
about him written

00:11:57.490 --> 00:11:59.590 align:middle line:90%
by a guy named Monaghan.

00:11:59.590 --> 00:12:01.870 align:middle line:84%
And they talk about
the conch shell beauty,

00:12:01.870 --> 00:12:03.861 align:middle line:84%
where the true story is
he went into a tavern.

00:12:03.861 --> 00:12:05.860 align:middle line:84%
And he saw one of the
most beautiful young woman

00:12:05.860 --> 00:12:07.090 align:middle line:90%
he'd ever seen.

00:12:07.090 --> 00:12:09.160 align:middle line:84%
He joked her face was
a color a conch shell--

00:12:09.160 --> 00:12:10.540 align:middle line:90%
this is in the biography.

00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:12.610 align:middle line:84%
And he swore an oath at
the Continental Congress

00:12:12.610 --> 00:12:14.276 align:middle line:84%
he'd never tell anyone
where she worked,

00:12:14.276 --> 00:12:15.580 align:middle line:90%
because she was so pretty.

00:12:15.580 --> 00:12:16.870 align:middle line:90%
Move forward-- 20th century.

00:12:16.870 --> 00:12:18.940 align:middle line:84%
A four-year-old boy's
walking along a beach

00:12:18.940 --> 00:12:21.400 align:middle line:84%
in southern Florida, looks
down and sees a shell,

00:12:21.400 --> 00:12:23.450 align:middle line:84%
turns to his nanny
and says, what's that?

00:12:23.450 --> 00:12:25.360 align:middle line:84%
And she says, honey,
that's a conch shell.

00:12:25.360 --> 00:12:27.070 align:middle line:84%
And the boy looks
at it and says,

00:12:27.070 --> 00:12:29.280 align:middle line:84%
can a lady's face be a
color of a conch shell?

00:12:29.280 --> 00:12:29.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Whoa.

00:12:29.620 --> 00:12:30.900 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: And two years
later, that boy had a reading

00:12:30.900 --> 00:12:32.650 align:middle line:90%
and was told he'd been John Jay.

00:12:32.650 --> 00:12:34.630 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's how
karmic memory works.

00:12:34.630 --> 00:12:37.510 align:middle line:84%
We take with us memories of
things that happened to us.

00:12:37.510 --> 00:12:39.320 align:middle line:84%
And we respond to
them in the present.

00:12:39.320 --> 00:12:41.860 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: How do you end,
Kevin, your Akashic records?

00:12:41.860 --> 00:12:43.552 align:middle line:84%
How does that book
finally close?

00:12:43.552 --> 00:12:45.010 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
I think it closes

00:12:45.010 --> 00:12:46.384 align:middle line:84%
when we reach
enlightenment, when

00:12:46.384 --> 00:12:49.019 align:middle line:84%
we reach perfection,
when we become all

00:12:49.019 --> 00:12:50.060 align:middle line:90%
that we were meant to be.

00:12:50.060 --> 00:12:51.910 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Is that
the heavenly state?

00:12:51.910 --> 00:12:55.180 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: I think it's a state
of an awareness of our oneness

00:12:55.180 --> 00:12:56.430 align:middle line:90%
with God--

00:12:56.430 --> 00:13:00.370 align:middle line:84%
might refer to it as the
Buddha's Bodhisattva vow,

00:13:00.370 --> 00:13:02.350 align:middle line:84%
as Jesus' reaching
enlightenment,

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:03.260 align:middle line:90%
becoming the Christ.

00:13:03.260 --> 00:13:05.050 align:middle line:84%
I think that's where
we're all headed.

00:13:05.050 --> 00:13:07.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Because I've always
believed that reincarnation

00:13:07.930 --> 00:13:11.470 align:middle line:84%
stops when you reach
that level of perfection

00:13:11.470 --> 00:13:13.140 align:middle line:84%
when there's no
need to reincarnate.

00:13:13.140 --> 00:13:13.940 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: Yeah.

00:13:13.940 --> 00:13:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Then I think, at some point,
you think, you know what?

00:13:16.420 --> 00:13:18.460 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to go back and help
some of those who haven't yet

00:13:18.460 --> 00:13:19.260 align:middle line:90%
made it.

00:13:19.260 --> 00:13:20.407 align:middle line:90%
So it's an ongoing process.

00:13:20.407 --> 00:13:22.990 align:middle line:84%
I kind of joke sometimes that,
if you can think of the dumbest

00:13:22.990 --> 00:13:25.240 align:middle line:84%
person you know-- until
everyone's made it,

00:13:25.240 --> 00:13:26.650 align:middle line:90%
we're probably not finished yet.

00:13:26.650 --> 00:13:28.358 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: So what's it
mean if you pass on

00:13:28.358 --> 00:13:30.040 align:middle line:84%
and your Akashic
records is maybe

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:32.930 align:middle line:84%
that thick as opposed
to somebody else's

00:13:32.930 --> 00:13:34.360 align:middle line:90%
who might be that thick?

00:13:34.360 --> 00:13:36.220 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well, I
think it's unlikely

00:13:36.220 --> 00:13:38.260 align:middle line:84%
that we have very
few experiences.

00:13:38.260 --> 00:13:40.300 align:middle line:84%
I think we've all come
back many, many times.

00:13:40.300 --> 00:13:43.920 align:middle line:84%
But I think that, if you haven't
had a lot of experiences,

00:13:43.920 --> 00:13:46.360 align:middle line:84%
the universe will give you
the opportunity at some point.

00:13:46.360 --> 00:13:49.990 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why can't somebody
from the other side step

00:13:49.990 --> 00:13:55.639 align:middle line:84%
in and solve some problems
here before they occur?

00:13:55.639 --> 00:13:57.430 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well, I
think, on the one hand,

00:13:57.430 --> 00:13:59.590 align:middle line:84%
even God doesn't interfere
with our free will.

00:13:59.590 --> 00:14:02.200 align:middle line:84%
But I also think that each and
every one of us at all times

00:14:02.200 --> 00:14:03.929 align:middle line:90%
are provided with guidance.

00:14:03.929 --> 00:14:05.720 align:middle line:84%
Cayce would say, we're
wired with guidance.

00:14:05.720 --> 00:14:08.680 align:middle line:84%
So I think we, oftentimes, have
the sense of what we should do,

00:14:08.680 --> 00:14:11.210 align:middle line:84%
but we don't necessarily
always follow through on it.

00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:11.530 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Interesting.

00:14:11.530 --> 00:14:12.880 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Sometimes,
we're afraid to speak up.

00:14:12.880 --> 00:14:15.440 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes, we don't think
we can do anything about it.

00:14:15.440 --> 00:14:17.560 align:middle line:84%
But I think each of us
can truly have a hand

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:18.700 align:middle line:90%
in transforming the world.

00:14:18.700 --> 00:14:20.440 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Back in my
Los Angeles office,

00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:22.720 align:middle line:84%
Kevin, I have a book
from Edgar Cayce,

00:14:22.720 --> 00:14:26.490 align:middle line:84%
of course, on some of
his health readings.

00:14:26.490 --> 00:14:27.610 align:middle line:90%
And it's uncanny.

00:14:27.610 --> 00:14:30.550 align:middle line:84%
And as you well know,
there are companies now

00:14:30.550 --> 00:14:35.660 align:middle line:84%
that produce health products
based on Cayce's readings,

00:14:35.660 --> 00:14:37.660 align:middle line:84%
which are all natural and
holistic, aren't they?

00:14:37.660 --> 00:14:38.535 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: They are.

00:14:38.535 --> 00:14:40.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, if you go
to edgarcayce.org,

00:14:40.740 --> 00:14:42.580 align:middle line:84%
there's over 400
treatment protocols

00:14:42.580 --> 00:14:45.190 align:middle line:84%
on any illness, arthritis
to varicose veins,

00:14:45.190 --> 00:14:47.690 align:middle line:84%
that people can look up
to see what Cayce what

00:14:47.690 --> 00:14:49.840 align:middle line:84%
a recommended 70,
80, 90 years ago.

00:14:49.840 --> 00:14:51.410 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: How accurate was he?

00:14:51.410 --> 00:14:53.350 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
from what we can tell,

00:14:53.350 --> 00:14:56.230 align:middle line:84%
he had at least a
95% accuracy rate.

00:14:56.230 --> 00:14:57.400 align:middle line:90%
He could tune into a person.

00:14:57.400 --> 00:14:59.440 align:middle line:90%
He could diagnose their illness.

00:14:59.440 --> 00:15:02.110 align:middle line:84%
He did say, however, that the
intent of the person getting

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:04.420 align:middle line:84%
a reading had a great deal
to do with the accuracy.

00:15:04.420 --> 00:15:06.970 align:middle line:84%
So a mother looking for
help for her sick child

00:15:06.970 --> 00:15:09.160 align:middle line:84%
would have a higher
caliber of accuracy

00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:11.920 align:middle line:84%
than someone wanting to know
where to dig for an oil well.

00:15:11.920 --> 00:15:14.766 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why was he called the
Father of Holistic Medicine?

00:15:14.766 --> 00:15:17.140 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Because he drew
from every school of medicine

00:15:17.140 --> 00:15:18.015 align:middle line:90%
that you can imagine.

00:15:18.015 --> 00:15:20.830 align:middle line:84%
He drew from a
pharmacopoeia, from surgery,

00:15:20.830 --> 00:15:24.770 align:middle line:84%
from allopathic medicine,
homeopathy, acupuncture,

00:15:24.770 --> 00:15:26.170 align:middle line:90%
massage, everything.

00:15:26.170 --> 00:15:28.660 align:middle line:84%
And his dream was to have a
hospital, which was originally

00:15:28.660 --> 00:15:30.320 align:middle line:84%
built in Virginia
Beach, Virginia,

00:15:30.320 --> 00:15:32.770 align:middle line:84%
where doctors and physicians
from every background--

00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:35.110 align:middle line:84%
nurses, therapists-- would
carry out the treatment.

00:15:35.110 --> 00:15:36.264 align:middle line:90%
And he would give readings.

00:15:36.264 --> 00:15:38.680 align:middle line:84%
And that's really why he moved
to Virginia Beach-- because

00:15:38.680 --> 00:15:39.540 align:middle line:90%
of the hospital.

00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And I got to tell you,
I practice a lot of things he

00:15:43.720 --> 00:15:44.800 align:middle line:90%
said about health--

00:15:44.800 --> 00:15:45.716 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: Excellent.

00:15:45.716 --> 00:15:49.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: --eating almonds
every day and items like that.

00:15:49.090 --> 00:15:50.200 align:middle line:90%
I'm into this.

00:15:50.200 --> 00:15:53.150 align:middle line:84%
I have been since I
was 11 or 12, too.

00:15:53.150 --> 00:15:58.474 align:middle line:90%
And it's remarkable.

00:15:58.474 --> 00:16:00.890 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Our current spa
has a lot of health protocols.

00:16:00.890 --> 00:16:02.620 align:middle line:90%
We do about 300 services a week.

00:16:02.620 --> 00:16:05.674 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing how many
older people are in ARE.

00:16:05.674 --> 00:16:07.090 align:middle line:84%
I think people who
are ARE members

00:16:07.090 --> 00:16:09.360 align:middle line:84%
tend to live longer for
following some of the Cayce

00:16:09.360 --> 00:16:09.910 align:middle line:90%
health protocols.

00:16:09.910 --> 00:16:11.530 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Yeah, what are
your demographics like--

