00:16:53.330 --> 00:16:58.270 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Now when Cayce was
giving his health readings,

00:16:58.270 --> 00:17:00.640 align:middle line:84%
he seemed to specialize
in health readings.

00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:02.020 align:middle line:90%
Why was it that?

00:17:02.020 --> 00:17:06.220 align:middle line:84%
Why did he specialize in
health as opposed to financial

00:17:06.220 --> 00:17:07.054 align:middle line:90%
or things like that?

00:17:07.054 --> 00:17:08.636 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Well,
he did give readings

00:17:08.636 --> 00:17:09.960 align:middle line:90%
on everything you can imagine.

00:17:09.960 --> 00:17:10.440 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Everything.

00:17:10.440 --> 00:17:11.200 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:17:11.200 --> 00:17:12.880 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Originally, what
happened was so many people

00:17:12.880 --> 00:17:14.829 align:middle line:84%
came to Mr. Cayce
as a last resort--

00:17:14.829 --> 00:17:17.187 align:middle line:84%
they'd been to doctors
and couldn't get help.

00:17:17.187 --> 00:17:18.520 align:middle line:90%
They'd gone to their physicians.

00:17:18.520 --> 00:17:20.079 align:middle line:84%
They'd gone to
specialized hospitals.

00:17:20.079 --> 00:17:21.430 align:middle line:90%
And no one could help them.

00:17:21.430 --> 00:17:24.490 align:middle line:84%
And there was this physician
in Hopkinsville, Kentucky

00:17:24.490 --> 00:17:26.800 align:middle line:84%
that wrote a paper
about Cayce and how he

00:17:26.800 --> 00:17:28.630 align:middle line:90%
became a doctor under hypnosis.

00:17:28.630 --> 00:17:30.730 align:middle line:84%
And that was picked up
by "The New York Times."

00:17:30.730 --> 00:17:33.310 align:middle line:84%
And after that, Cayce was
really seen as a place

00:17:33.310 --> 00:17:34.570 align:middle line:90%
to go as a last resort.

00:17:34.570 --> 00:17:38.920 align:middle line:84%
And about 9,000 of the
14,000 readings we have

00:17:38.920 --> 00:17:39.979 align:middle line:90%
are about health.

00:17:39.979 --> 00:17:41.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: That is amazing.

00:17:41.020 --> 00:17:41.590 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: It is amazing.

00:17:41.590 --> 00:17:43.750 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And you say the
accuracy rate is pretty high?

00:17:43.750 --> 00:17:44.900 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: It is very high.

00:17:44.900 --> 00:17:46.960 align:middle line:84%
He could tune into a person's
blood pressure, temperature,

00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:47.410 align:middle line:90%
everything.

00:17:47.410 --> 00:17:49.390 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did he have
any medical background?

00:17:49.390 --> 00:17:51.098 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: He had no
medical background,

00:17:51.098 --> 00:17:52.344 align:middle line:90%
no medical background.

00:17:52.344 --> 00:17:54.760 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Nowadays, they'd nail
him for practicing medicine

00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:56.051 align:middle line:90%
without a license or something.

00:17:56.051 --> 00:17:58.180 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: He was actually
falsely arrested once

00:17:58.180 --> 00:18:00.390 align:middle line:84%
for practicing medicine
without a license when

00:18:00.390 --> 00:18:01.510 align:middle line:90%
he was in Detroit.

00:18:01.510 --> 00:18:05.140 align:middle line:84%
But he talked a lot about
other topics, like vibrations.

00:18:05.140 --> 00:18:07.060 align:middle line:84%
There's a wealth of
information on how

00:18:07.060 --> 00:18:10.210 align:middle line:84%
our thoughts, our activities
create a vibrational resonance.

00:18:10.210 --> 00:18:11.980 align:middle line:84%
And one of the examples
he gave-- that,

00:18:11.980 --> 00:18:14.310 align:middle line:84%
if you go into a church--
even if it's empty--

00:18:14.310 --> 00:18:17.020 align:middle line:84%
and then go into a post
office-- even if it's empty--

00:18:17.020 --> 00:18:19.120 align:middle line:84%
that there's a different
energy in that room.

00:18:19.120 --> 00:18:21.550 align:middle line:84%
And one of our jobs
as a human creature

00:18:21.550 --> 00:18:23.950 align:middle line:84%
is to create a higher level
of vibration that can help

00:18:23.950 --> 00:18:25.725 align:middle line:90%
eventually transform the world.

00:18:25.725 --> 00:18:27.100 align:middle line:84%
And that's really
why we're here,

00:18:27.100 --> 00:18:29.260 align:middle line:90%
to bring spirit into the Earth.

00:18:29.260 --> 00:18:32.590 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: What would you say
he was like as a human being?

00:18:32.590 --> 00:18:34.390 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: He loved to garden.

00:18:34.390 --> 00:18:36.730 align:middle line:90%
He loved to golf.

00:18:36.730 --> 00:18:37.660 align:middle line:90%
He loved to bowl.

00:18:37.660 --> 00:18:41.350 align:middle line:84%
He loved to pull together
fruits, and berries, and jams.

00:18:41.350 --> 00:18:43.330 align:middle line:90%
He loved to read the Bible.

00:18:43.330 --> 00:18:45.040 align:middle line:90%
He was a great photographer.

00:18:45.040 --> 00:18:49.510 align:middle line:84%
He loved to talk to
people and have friends.

00:18:49.510 --> 00:18:51.340 align:middle line:84%
He had pictures of
all kinds of people

00:18:51.340 --> 00:18:52.540 align:middle line:90%
all over his office wall.

00:18:52.540 --> 00:18:56.950 align:middle line:84%
So he was very much a people
person, down to Earth,

00:18:56.950 --> 00:19:00.170 align:middle line:84%
loved to read the Bible,
loved to teach Sunday school--

00:19:00.170 --> 00:19:00.970 align:middle line:90%
just a regular--

00:19:00.970 --> 00:19:01.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: So a nice guy.

00:19:01.750 --> 00:19:03.166 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: He was
a very nice guy

00:19:03.166 --> 00:19:04.549 align:middle line:90%
who had this incredible gift.

00:19:04.549 --> 00:19:07.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Had a son, Edgar Evans,
who passed away a few years.

00:19:07.090 --> 00:19:08.256 align:middle line:90%
>>TODESCHI: He had two sons.

00:19:08.256 --> 00:19:10.360 align:middle line:10%
He had an older son,
Hugh Lynn Cayce--

00:19:10.360 --> 00:19:13.174 align:middle line:10%
who really took the organization
that had 300 members when his

00:19:13.174 --> 00:19:15.340 align:middle line:10%
father died and turned it
into one that's now around

00:19:15.340 --> 00:19:16.140 align:middle line:10%
the world--

00:19:16.140 --> 00:19:18.130 align:middle line:10%
And Edgar Evans Cayce,
the younger son,

00:19:18.130 --> 00:19:20.269 align:middle line:10%
who actually was
a lifelong member

00:19:20.269 --> 00:19:21.310 align:middle line:10%
of our board of trustees.

00:19:21.310 --> 00:19:22.768 align:middle line:84%
And he passed away
a few years ago.

00:19:22.768 --> 00:19:24.790 align:middle line:84%
He worked for the
energy company.

00:19:24.790 --> 00:19:28.272 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Did they possess
their father's reading ability?

00:19:28.272 --> 00:19:30.730 align:middle line:84%
>>TODESCHI: Neither one of them
were professional psychics.

00:19:30.730 --> 00:19:32.710 align:middle line:84%
But the Cayce material
talks about how

00:19:32.710 --> 00:19:35.790 align:middle line:84%
we are all psychic and
gives a lot of information

00:19:35.790 --> 00:19:38.650 align:middle line:84%
on how we could work with
psychic ability in our dreams,

00:19:38.650 --> 00:19:41.530 align:middle line:84%
improve our intuition,
work with synchronicity.

00:19:41.530 --> 00:19:43.240 align:middle line:84%
So lots of what we
do is teach people

00:19:43.240 --> 00:19:45.414 align:middle line:84%
how they can access their
own intuitive gifts.

